<TITLE> Buoyant Zimbabwe face tough Sri Lanka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 11 (bdnews24.com)  Upbeat Zimbabwe take on tough Sri Lanka in the second match of the Tri-Nation Cup at Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium on Monday. Zimbabwe are flying high after a 38-run win against hosts Bangladesh in the series opener that almost threw them into the final. They want to push Sri Lanka in the second match. Skipper Prosper Utseya said they were looking forward to playing the kind of positive cricket that they had displayed against Bangladesh, who will certainly pray an unlikely loss of Sri Lanka. If Sri Lanka lose to Zimbabwe, Bangladesh have a opportunity to play the final, if they beat Sri Lanka in the final group match on Wednesday. Zimbabwe are also seeking inspirations from home matches they played against Sri Lanka, who had laboured hard to win by five runs, two wickets and 19 runs in the last three matches out of five ODIs in November. "If we could convert the half chances into full tomorrow (Monday), we can hope a good result against Sri Lanka," said the 22-year old captain, one of main architects of Saturday's win against Bangladesh. Sri Lankan captain Mahela Jayawardene, however, felt no pressure taking on Zimbabwe. He said there was no extra concern over the match as they took the game as usual The Lankan captain, however, seemed a bit worried over the new guys, who have no experience to play in Mirpur. He hoped they would cope with the condition and deliver their best
